9 An Act relating to children; amending 10A O.S. 2021,
Sections 2-2-101 and 2-3-103, as amended by Section
10 1, Chapter 242, O.S.L. 2022 (10A O.S. Supp. 2025,
Section 2-3-103), which relates to the Oklahoma
11 Juvenile Code; providing that certain children shall
be considered to be in the temporary custody of the
12 Office of Juvenile Affairs under certain
circumstances; providing exception; requiring the
13 Office to provide all medication prescribed for
juveniles at time of placement; providing temporary
14 exception if medication is not available; directing
the Office to provide medication within certain time
15 period; and providing an effective date.
